history.content: It's doable, but I personally wouldn't recommend it. 161 and 186 have both had their difficulties raised and 162 by itself is a doozy.

children.subject:
@David Niu

Not sure if it'll tag or not.. How much have 161/186 been raised by? In what way workload etc

Thanks
Is is more proof heavy than 174? Was thinking the probability would be useful for ML ..

174 is significantly less workload than other upper-div problem set type classes; I'd say the problem sets take ~5 hours a week (most of the solutions are slight tweaks to things in the textbook). Don't know about 152 so can't comment.
Does 186 have any actual database usage or are the assignments mainly recreating one?

The first "project" this semester was a practical use of sql for baseball statistics. After that it was all designing parts of a database system (creating indexes which is a type of data structure for storing/sorting data, implementing efficient join algorithms, creating a query optimizer, creating a lock management system). So no building database applications. Theres a lot of useful stuff (understanding a DBMS, concurrency/locking, parallelism, SQL, sorting/hashing large files) that you'll learn which is fairly ubiquitous even if you don't go into databases. Unfortunately, there is a lot of stuff that's mostly not useful to you in industry if you don't work on building databases (understanding how more advanced join algorithms work like hybrid hashing).

@anon I'm taking 188, 170 and 186 together this semester with an r5b (so somewhat comparable workload). 170 has psets every week which really aren't too bad (varies between weeks, some are pretty easy, some are very hard). 186 this semester is a course you can kind of forget you're taking during intervals. There are 5 projects/hws which aren't too difficult and don't really take up a lot of time (the instructions are usually very good). I usually catch up on material by watching lectures a week before a test and look over old tests a few days before. I don't know what it was like before, but I would say it's about equal to 188 in workload. Very manageable, and I'm not great with time management and maintaining motivation.
